{"topic": "OpenZWave/1/node/8/", "msg": "{\n    \"NodeID\": 8,\n    \"NodeQueryStage\": \"Complete\",\n    \"isListening\": true,\n    \"isFlirs\": false,\n    \"isBeaming\": true,\n    \"isRouting\": true,\n    \"isSecurityv1\": false,\n    \"isZWavePlus\": true,\n    \"isNIFRecieved\": true,\n    \"isAwake\": true,\n    \"isFailed\": false,\n    \"MetaData\": {\n        \"OZWInfoURL\": \"http://www.openzwave.com/device-database/0315:3034:4447\",\n        \"ZWAProductURL\": \"\",\n        \"ProductPic\": \"images/zwp/WD-100.png\",\n        \"Description\": \"ZLINK\u2019s WD-100 is a Z-Wave Plus certified device with S2 security and SmartStart features. You can now add this device securely and with ease using QR code on the product with compatible gateways supporting S2 and Smart Start. The elegant WD-100, with 7 LED dim level lights, communicates with other Z-Wave certified devices and updates your home into a smart home. WD-100 replaces a standard in-wall light switch turning it into a Z-Wave controlled network device with manual and remote control dimming and On/Off light control. ZLINK WD-100 supports, \u201cInstant Feedback\u201d of manual status to compatible gateways as well as Central Scene to allow setting multiple scene control throughout the home, with gateways supporting Central Scene. Each Z-Wave device serves as a node to repeat the signal in the network, thus, extending the overall Z-Wave mesh wireless network range. Additional Features: \u2022 Power 120 VAC, 60Hz, up to 600 watts \u2022 Region US: 908.4, 916 MHz \u2022 Works w/ most incandescent, dimmable CFL & LED lights \u2022 7 segment LED dim level indicator \u2022 Remotely or manually turns ON or OFF, or DIM lights \u2022 Fits standard wall plates (wall plate not included) \u2022 Works with any certified gateway supporting Z-Wave\",\n        \"ProductManualURL\": \"https://Products.Z-WaveAlliance.org/ProductManual/File?folder=&filename=Manuals/2808/ZL-WD-100 UG v3.pdf\",\n        \"ProductPageURL\": \"\",\n        \"InclusionHelp\": \"Place your Z-Wave controller in \\\"Inclusion\\\" mode. Then tap either the top or bottom paddle once to initiation Inclusion.\",\n        \"ExclusionHelp\": \"Place your Z-Wave controller in \\\"Exclusion\\\" mode. Then tap either the top or bottom paddle once to initiation Exclusion.\",\n        \"ResetHelp\": \"1. Turn the connected light ON with the rocker 2. Quickly tap the topside of the rocker 3 times 3. Then quickly tap the bottom side of the rocker 3 times If you see the lights turn OFF then ON it means that the module has been rest successfully.
